If you&#39;re doing all the updates in an event callback, you should use 
wait for idle to make sure the event has been processed

T.

On Wednesday, May 8, 2002, at 04:08 PM, Tom Ayerst wrote:

&gt; I am having a strange, intermittent problem with jfcunit (downloaded
&gt; from CVS on Saturday).
&gt;
&gt; I have a test:
&gt;
&gt;     public void testOneValue() throws Exception {
&gt;         m_helper.sendString(this, m_controller, &quot;2&quot;);
&gt;         assertEquals(&quot;Not set correctly&quot;, &quot;2&quot;, m_controller.getText());
&gt;         Thread.sleep(1000);
&gt;         m_helper.sendKeyAction(this, m_controller, KeyEvent.VK_ENTER);
&gt;         Thread.sleep(1000);
&gt;         awtSleep();
&gt;         Thread.sleep(1000);
&gt;
&gt;         assertEquals(&quot;Model not updated&quot;, new Integer(2),
&gt; m_model.getData().lastElement());
&gt;         assertEquals(&quot;Controller not cleared&quot;, &quot;&quot;,
&gt; m_controller.getText());
&gt;         assertEquals(&quot;Not updated correctly&quot;,  &quot;2.0&quot;,
&gt; m_averageView.getText());
&gt;         assertEquals(&quot;Not updated correctly&quot;,  &quot;2&#92;n&quot;,
&gt; m_listOfValuesView.getText());
&gt;     }
&gt;
&gt; That runs against a simple MVC gui where the controller is a JTextField.
&gt;  The model is connected to it via an ActionListener.
&gt;
&gt; When I run it the model is usually not updated, occasionally it is (I
&gt; cannot reproduce it at will).  The second test assertEquals(&quot;Model not
&gt; updated&quot;...) fails.
&gt;
&gt; Can anyone give me a hint as to what is going on?  I am sure I am
&gt; missing something obvious but I am not sure what.
&gt;
&gt; Thanks.
&gt;
&gt; Tom
